<p><strong>Solar Energy Fundamentals and Applications by H.P. Garg PDF: Key Questions and Answers</strong></p>
<p>H.P. Garg's comprehensive text, "Solar Energy Fundamentals and Applications," delves into the intricacies of solar energy. Here are five fundamental questions addressed in the book:</p>
<p><strong>1. What is Solar Energy?</strong>
Solar energy is the radiant energy emitted by the sun. It consists of a spectrum of electromagnetic waves, including visible light, ultraviolet radiation, and infrared radiation.</p>
<p><strong>2. How Can Solar Energy Be Harvested?</strong>
Solar energy can be harnessed through photovoltaic cells, which convert light energy directly into electrical energy. Solar thermal collectors can also be used to convert sunlight into heat, which can be utilized for various purposes, such as heating water or generating steam.</p>
<p><strong>3. What are the Advantages of Solar Energy?</strong>
Solar energy is a renewable and sustainable source of energy. It is inexhaustible, non-polluting, and can be harnessed virtually anywhere with sunlight. Moreover, the cost of solar panels has been declining significantly, making it an increasingly affordable option.</p>
<p><strong>4. What are the Applications of Solar Energy?</strong>
Solar energy finds widespread applications in various sectors. It can be used to power homes, businesses, and vehicles. Solar water heaters, solar lighting, and solar cooking are also popular applications.</p>
<p><strong>5. What are the Challenges Associated with Solar Energy?</strong>
Intermittency is a key challenge with solar energy as it relies on sunlight availability. The cost of solar installations can also be a barrier to widespread adoption. Additionally, the integration of solar energy into existing energy grids may require infrastructure modifications.</p>